<paragraph id="IAS24_BC6" base="SL9061100" principles="no"><paranum>BC6</paranum><prolog><data name="standard_number" value="IAS 24"/><data name="paranum" value="BC6"/></prolog><body><p id="IAS24_P0296">Because the Board&#x2019;s intention was not to reconsider the fundamental approach to related party disclosures established by IAS 24, this Basis for Conclusions discusses only the following requirements in IAS 24:</p><ol id="IAS24_L0025" base="SL9061101" type="lower-alpha"><li><li_value>(a)</li_value> <p id="IAS24_P0297" base="SL9061103">management compensation (<xref id="IAS24_X0210" base="SL13817137" href="IAS24_gBC7-BC10.dita#IAS24_gBC7-BC10">paragraphs BC7&#x2013;BC10</xref>);</p></li><li><li_value>(b)</li_value> <p id="IAS24_P0298" base="SL9061105">related party disclosures in separate financial statements (<xref id="IAS24_X0211" base="SL13817129" href="IAS24_gBC11-BC17.dita#IAS24_gBC11-BC17">paragraphs BC11&#x2013;BC17</xref>);</p></li><li><li_value>(c)</li_value> <p id="IAS24_P0299" base="SL9061107">definition of a related party (<xref id="IAS24_X0212" base="SL13817133" href="IAS24_gBC18-BC32.dita#IAS24_gBC18-BC32">paragraphs BC18&#x2013;BC32</xref>);</p></li><li><li_value>(d)</li_value> <p id="IAS24_P0300" base="SL9061109">government&#x2011;related entities (<xref id="IAS24_X0213" base="SL13817141" href="IAS24_gBC33-BC48.dita#IAS24_gBC33-BC48">paragraphs BC33&#x2013;BC48</xref>); and</p></li><li><li_value>(e)</li_value> <p id="IAS24_P0301" base="SL9061111">other minor changes made in 2009 (<xref id="IAS24_X0214" base="SL13817145" href="IAS24_BC49.dita#IAS24_BC49">paragraph BC49</xref>).</p></li></ol></body></paragraph>